[00:02.36]Lyrics by：Luke Combs/Dan Isbell/Tyler King/Drew Parker
[00:05.74]Composed by：Luke Combs/Dan Isbell/Tyler King/Drew Parker
[00:09.11]Luke Combs：
[00:09.49]Well I got a call from Rowdy 'round six o'clock
[00:12.79]Sayin' he caught a hankerin' for a honky tonk
[00:15.90]Wants an ice cold beer and a country song
[00:19.13]But he didn't want to stay out all night long
[00:22.81]Well I ain't the kind to let a buddy drink alone
[00:25.56]But I can't turn it off once I turn it on
[00:28.49]Luke Combs：
[00:28.81]There's no stoppin' me once I get goin'
[00:32.20]Put a can in my hand man I'm wide a*s open
[00:35.69]The tick-tock of that clock is like a time bomb
[00:41.86]By half past 10 I'm half past tipsy
[00:45.45]And quarter to 12 man I done had plenty
[00:48.67]The countdowns on when the first beer hits me
[00:52.06]5-4-3-2-1 too many

[00:09.49]六点钟左右 我接到Rowdy打来的电话
[00:12.79]他说想去酒吧喝一杯
